ennessee Tech Golden Eagles|title=Tennessee Tech}}\n| site_stadium = Legion Field\n| site_cityst = Birmingham, AL\n| tv = \n| score = 38\u201314\n| attend = 8,765\n}}\n|{{CFB schedule entry\n| date = November 22\n| time = 2:00 p.m.\n| w/l = w\n| away = y\n| opponent = [[1997 Arkansas State Indians football team|Arkansas State]]\n| site_stadium = [[Indian Stadium]]\n| site_cityst = [[Jonesboro, Arkansas|Jonesboro, AR]]\n| tv = \n| score = 13\u20137\n| attend = 7,318\n}}\n}}\n<ref name=\"MediaGuide\">{{cite web|title=2008 UAB Football Media Guide: Records & History I|url=http://uabsports.cstv.com/auto_pdf/p_hotos/s_chools/albr/sports/m-footbl/auto_pdf/RecordsHistoryI-08|publisher=University of Alabama at Birmingham Sports Information|accessdate=September 19, 2008|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20080928102421/http://uabsports.cstv.com/auto_pdf/p_hotos/s_chools/albr/sports/m-footbl/auto_pdf/RecordsHistoryI-08|archivedate=September 28, 2008|url-status=dead}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n{{UAB Blazers football navbox}}\n\n[[Category:1997 NCAA Division I-A independents football season|UAB]]\n[[Category:UAB Blazers football seasons]]\n[[Category:1997 in sports in Alabama|UAB Football]]\n\n{{collegefootball-1990s-season-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{short description|American college football season}}\n{{Infobox NCAA team season\n  |year=1997\n  |team=UAB Blazers\n  |image=\n  |image_size=\n  |conference=Independent\n  |short_conf=\n  |record=5\u20136\n  |conf_record=\n  |head_coach=[[Watson Brown]]\n  |hc_year=3rd\n  |stadium=[[Legion Field]]<br>(Capacity: 83,091)\n}}\n{{1997 Division I-A independents football standings}}\nThe '''1997 UAB Blazers football team''' represented the [[University of Alabama at Birmingham]] (UAB) in the [[1997 NCAA Division I-A football season]], and was the seventh team fielded by the school. The team's [[head coach]] was [[Watson Brown]], who entered his third season as the UAB's head coach. They played their home games at [[Legion Field]] in [[Birmingham, Alabama]] and competed as a [[Division I-A]] [[NCAA Division I-FBS independent schools|Independent]]. The Blazers finished their second season at the I-A level with a record of 5\u20136.\n\n==Schedule==\n{{CFB schedule\n| rankyear = 1997\n| poll = AP\n| timezone = Central\n\n|{{CFB schedule entry\n| date = August 28\n| time = 7:00 p.m.\n| w/l = l\n| away = y\n| opponent = [[1997 Kansas Jayhawks football team|Kansas]]\n| site_stadium = [[Memorial Stadium (University of Kansas)|Memorial Stadium]]\n| site_cityst = [[Lawrence, Kansas|Lawrence, KS]]\n| tv = \n| score = 0\u201324\n| attend = 32,100\n}}\n|{{CFB schedule entry\n| date = September 6\n| time = 7:00 p.m.\n| w/l = l\n| away = y\n| opponent = [[1997 Memphis Tigers football team|Memphis]]\n| gamename = Battle for the Bones\n| site_stadium = [[Liberty Bowl Memorial Stadium]]\n| site_cityst = [[Memphis, Tennessee|Memphis, TN]]\n| tv = \n| score = 7\u201328\n| attend = 24,108\n}}\n|{{CFB schedule entry\n| date = September 13\n| time = 9:00 p.m.\n| w/l = l\n| away = y\n| opponent = [[1997 Arizona Wildcats football team|Arizona]]\n| site_stadium = [[Arizona Stadium]]\n| site_cityst = [[Tucson, Arizona|Tucson, AZ]]\n| tv = \n| score = 10\u201324\n| attend = 36,309\n}}\n|{{CFB schedule entry\n| date = September 20\n| time = 7:00 p.m.\n| w/l = w\n| opponent = {{cfb link|year=1997|team=Jacksonville State Gamecocks|title=Jacksonville State}}\n| site_stadium = [[Legion Field]]\n| site_cityst = [[Birmingham, Alabama|Birmingham, AL]]\n| tv = \n| score = 34\u201316\n| attend = 23,775\n}}\n|{{CFB schedule entry\n| date = September 27\n| time = 7:00 p.m.\n| w/l = w\n| away = y\n| opponent = {{cfb link|year=1997|team=Southwestern Louisiana Ragin' Cajuns|title=Southwestern Louisiana}}\n| site_stadium = [[Cajun Field]]\n| site_cityst = [[Lafayette, Louisiana|Lafayette, LA]]\n| tv = \n| score = 42\u20137\n| attend = 15,024\n}}\n|{{CFB schedule entry\n| date = October 4\n| time = 7:00 p.m.\n| w/l = w\n| ho