80625155129162396f86779c5_2|work=Seconomy|date=June 25, 2018|accessdate=June 25, 2018|language=ko|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180625213939/http://www.seconomy.kr/view.php?ud=20180625155129162396f86779c5_2|archive-date=June 25, 2018|url-status=live}}</ref> This marked his first fixed travel show since ''MAPS'' in 2015.<ref name=\":57\"/><ref name=\":58\"/> He was also cast in his second game show, ''[[Begin A Game]]'' in October 2018.<ref name=\":48\">{{Cite news|title='\ube44\uae34\uc5b4\uac8c\uc784' \uae40\ud76c\ucca0\u00b7\uc2e0\ub3d9\u00b7\uae40\uc900\ud604\u00b7\uae30\uc6a4\u00b7\uacf5\ucc2c\u00b7\uc870\ud604 MC \ud655\uc815! 11\uc6d4 2\uc77c(\uae08) \uccab \ubc29\uc1a1!|url=http://enews.imbc.com/News/RetrieveNewsInfo/245357|work=Imbc enews|date=October 17, 2018|accessdate=October 17, 2018|language=ko|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181017123528/http://enews.imbc.com/News/RetrieveNewsInfo/245357|archive-date=October 17, 2018|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nIn February 2018, following the success of \"Sweet Dream\", Universe Cowards returned with \"[[Falling Blossoms]]\".<ref>{{cite web|title=Super Junior's Kim Heechul and Min Kyunghoon Give Visibility to Developmentally Disabled People in 'Falling Blossoms' Video|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/k-town/8206111/super-junior-kim-heechul-min-kyunghoon-falling-blossoms-video|website=Billboard|publisher=|date=February 18, 2018|accessdate=June 16, 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180616113637/https://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/k-town/8206111/super-junior-kim-heechul-min-kyunghoon-falling-blossoms-video|archive-date=June 16, 2018|url-status=live}}</ref> The song is part of ''Knowing Bros'' music video competition.<ref>{{cite news |last1=Jung |first1=Yoo-jin |title=\uae40\ud76c\ucca0X\ubbfc\uacbd\ud6c8 \uc6b0\uc8fc \uac81\uc7c1\uc774, \uc2e0\uace1 MV\uc11c '\ube0c\ub85c\ub9e8\uc2a4' \uc608\uace0 |trans-title=Kim Hee-chul x Min Kyung-hoon Universe Cowards, New Song's MV Bromance Teaser |url=http://news1.kr/articles/?3232833 |accessdate=June 21, 2018 |work=New 1 |date=February 10, 2018 |language=ko |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180622004958/http://news1.kr/articles/?3232833 |archive-date=June 22, 2018 |url-status=live }}</ref> Min Kyung-hoon wrote the lyrics to \"Falling Blossoms\" with his Buzz bandmates Yoo Woo-hyun and Shin Joon-ki.<ref>{{cite news |last1=Lee |first1=Yoo-na |title=\uc6b0\uc8fc\uac81\uc7c1\uc774 \ubbfc\uacbd\ud6c8X\uae40\ud76c\ucca0, '\ub098\ube44\uc7a0' \uc787\ub294 \uc2e0\uace1 '\ud6c4\uc720\uc99d' \ubc1c\ub9e4 |trans-title=Universe Cowards Min Kyung-hoon x Kim Hee-chul, Release of A New Song titled \"Falling Blossoms\" following \"Sweet Dream\" |url=http://sports.chosun.com/news/ntype.htm?id=201802180100143950010917&servicedate=20180217 |accessdate=June 21, 2018 |work=Sports Chosun |date=February 17, 2018 |language=ko |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180622005042/http://sports.chosun.com/news/ntype.htm?id=201802180100143950010917&servicedate=20180217 |archive-date=June 22, 2018 |url-status=live }}</ref> The song peaked at number 15 on Gaon Digital Chart.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://gaonchart.co.kr/main/section/chart/online.gaon?nationGbn=T&serviceGbn=ALL&targetTime=&hitYear=&termGbn=week|title=Falling Blossoms|date=February 17, 2018|access-date=March 1, 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180303184417/http://gaonchart.co.kr/main/section/chart/online.gaon?nationGbn=T&serviceGbn=ALL&targetTime=&hitYear=&termGbn=week|archive-date=March 3, 2018|url-status=live}}</ref> In November, Heechul & Min Kyung-hoon were again nominated for Best Rock Song at the [[2018 Melon Music Awards|10th Melon Music Awards]], which they later won on December 1, making them the only artist to win the award two years in a row.<ref name=\":52\">{{cite news|url=http://star.hankookilbo.com/News/Read/201812012273345683|title='MMA' \ubc29\ud0c4\uc18c\ub144\ub2e8\u00b7\uc544\uc774\ucf58\u00b7\uc6cc\ub108\uc6d0, \uc62c\ud574 \uac00\uc694\uacc4 \ud729\uc4f4 '\ub300\uc0c1' [\uc885\ud569]|date=December 1, 2018|accessdate=December 1, 2018|publisher=Star Hankookilbo|language=ko|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181201181022/http://star.hankookilbo.com/News/Read/201812012273345683|archive-date=December 1, 2018|url-status=live}}</ref><ref name=\":53\">{{cite news|url=http://www.spotvnews.co.kr/?mod=news&act=articleView&idxno=251656|title=[2018 MMA] \ubc29\ud0c4\uc18c\ub144\ub2e8, 7\uad00\uc655\u2026\uc544\uc774\ucf58-\uc6cc\ub108\uc6d0 3\uad00\uc655 (\uc885\ud569)|date=December 1, 2018|accessdate=December 1, 2018|publisher=SpoTV News|language=ko}}</ref>\n\n=== 2019\u2013present: Solo music and established TV personalities ===\nHeechul's debut solo digital single, called \"Old Movie\", was released on April 24, 2019.<ref>{{cite news|title=[\uacf5\uc2dd]\uae40\ud76c\ucca0, 24\uc77c \uccab \uc194\ub85c \uc2f1\uae00 '\uc61b\ub0a0 \uc0ac\ub78c' \ubc1c\ud45c+\ud1a0\ud06c\uc1fc \uac1c\ucd5c|url=http://news.chosun.com/site/data/html_dir/2019/04/17/2019041701041.html|language=Korean|date=April 17, 2019|accessdate=April 17, 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190417030052/http://news.chosun.com/site/data/html_dir/2019/04/17/2019041701041.html|archive-date=April 17, 2019|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |last1=Park |first1=Hyun-taek |title=\uae40\ud76c\ucca0, \uc624\ub298 \uc2e0\uace1 '\uc61b\ub0a0 \uc0ac\ub78c', \uc74c\uc6d0\u00b7MV \uacf5\uac1c |url=http://www.edaily.co.kr/news/read?newsId=01243126622459400&mediaCodeNo=258 |access-date=May 16, 2019 |work=E Daily |date=April 24, 2019 |language=ko |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190424025314/http://www.edaily.co.kr/news/read?newsId=01243126622459400&mediaCodeNo=258 |archive-date=April 24, 2019 |url-status=live }}</ref> It subsequently topped the charts in seven different countries.<ref>{{cite news |last1=Ahn |first1=Jin-yong |title=\uae40\ud76c\ucca0 \uc2e0\uace1 '\uc61b\ub0a0 \uc0ac\ub78c', \uc544\uc774\ud2a0\uc988 \uc2f1\uae00 \ucc28\ud2b8 \uc804 \uc138\uacc4 7\uac1c \uc9c0\uc5ed\uc11c 1\uc704 |url=http://www.munhwa.com/news/view.html?no=20190425MW161832994198 |access-date=May 16, 2019 |work=Munhwa |date=April 25, 2019 |language=ko}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |last1=Choi |first1=Young-jae |title=\uae40\ud76c\ucca0 \uccab \uc194\ub85c\uace1 \ubc1c\ud45c 7\uac1c\uad6d \ub3d9\uc2dc 1\uc704 |url=http://www.kwnews.co.kr/nview.asp?s=601&aid=219042600069 |access-date=May 16, 2019 |work=Kw News |date=April 27, 2019 |language=ko}}</ref> On May 4 and 5, Heechul held his first talk show event, which sold-out in one minute from the start of the internet ticket booking.<ref>{{cite news |last1=Jo |first1=Hyun-joo |title=\ubcf8\uaca9 \ucd94\uc5b5\uc18c\ud658\uc1fc...'\uc6b0\uc8fc \ub300\uc2a4\ud0c0' \uae40\ud76c\ucca0, \uccab \ud1a0\ud06c\uc1fc \ub9c8\ubb34\ub9ac |url=https://www.ytn.co.kr/_sn/0117_201905061704596511 |access-date=May 16, 2019 |work=YTN |date=May 6, 2019 |language=ko}}</ref> In 2019, Heechul appeared in more than ten programs over the course of the year, and became a fixed cast member of the reality program ''[[My Little Old Boy]]''<ref>{{Cite news |script-title=ko:\uae40\ud76c\ucca0, \uc5b4\uba38\ub2c8\uc640 SBS '\ubbf8\uc6b4 \uc6b0\ub9ac \uc0c8\ub07c' \ud569\ub958|url=https://www.yna.co.kr/view/AKR20190822058400005|access-date=August 22, 2019|language=ko}}</ref>, ''[[Why Did You Come To My House]]?''<ref>{{Cite news |script-title=ko:\u2018\ud55c\ud61c\uc9c4-\uae40\ud76c\ucca0-\uae40\uc2e0\uc601-\uc624\uc2a4\ud2f4 \uac15' \uc2e0\uaddc\uc608\ub2a5 \u2018\uc6b0\ub9ac \uc9d1\uc5d0 \uc65c \uc654\ub2c8\u2019 \uc545\ub3d9 \uc9d1\ub4e4\uc774 \uba64\ubc84 \ud655\uc815|url=http://www.newsa.co.kr/news/articleView.html?idxno=215807#09Xb|date=April 26, 2019|access-date=April 26, 2019|language=ko}}</ref>, ''{{ill|A Man Who Feeds The Dog|ko|\uac1c\ubc25 \uc8fc\ub294 \ub0a8\uc790}}''<ref>{{Cite news|script-title=ko:\u2018\uac1c\ubb18\ud55c \uc5ec\ud589\u2019 8\uc6d4 \uc815\uaddc