ul]]\n[[Category:1983 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Sangji University alumni]]\n[[Category:21st-century South Korean singers]]\n[[Category:South Korean male idols]]\n[[Category:South Korean male pop singers]]\n[[Category:South Korean male film actors]]\n[[Category:South Korean male musical theatre actors]]\n[[Category:South Korean male television actors]]\n[[Category:South Korean television presenters]]\n[[Category:South Korean radio presenters]]\n[[Category:SM Entertainment artists]]\n[[Category:Super Junior members]]\n[[Category:Super Junior-T members]]\n[[Category:Kim Heechul & Kim Jungmo members]]\n[[Category:Weekly Idol members]]\n[[Category:Melon Music Award winners]]\n[[Category:King of Mask Singer contestants]]\n", "name_user": "EchizenRema", "label": "unsafe", "comment": "", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Kim_Hee-chul"}
{"title_page": "Mario Abrante", "text_new": "{{Spanish name|\u00c1lvarez|Abrante}}\n{{Infobox football biography\n| name = Mario\n| image = Mario 2011.jpg\n| image_size = 150\n| caption = Mario as a [[Real Betis|Betis]] player in 2011\n| fullname = Pedro Mario \u00c1lvarez Abrante<ref name=Bio>{{cite news|url=https://www.elmundo.es/elmundodeporte/envivos/fichas/1/020/4372.html|title=Pedro MARIO \u00c1lvarez Abrante|publisher=[[El Mundo (Spain)|El Mundo]]|language=Spanish|accessdate=17 April 2020}}</ref>\n| birth_date = {{birth date and age|1982|2|2|df=y}}<ref name=Bio/>\n| birth_place = [[Tenerife]], Spain<ref name=Bio/>\n| height = {{height|m=1.78}}<ref name=Bio/>\n| position = [[Defender (association football)#Centre-back|Centre back]]\n| currentclub = [[Atl\u00e9tico San Luis]]\n| clubnumber = 5\n| youthyears1 = | youthclubs1 = Longuera-Toscal\n| youthyears2 = 1998\u20131999 | youthclubs2 = [[Atl\u00e9tico Madrid]]\n| years1 = 1999\u20132000 | clubs1 = [[Atl\u00e9tico Madrid C]] | caps1 = | goals1 = \n| years2 = 2000\u20132001 | clubs2 = [[Atl\u00e9tico Madrid B]] | caps2 = 28 | goals2 = 0\n| years3 = 2001\u20132006 | clubs3 = [[Real Valladolid|Valladolid]] | caps3 = 90 | goals3 = 3\n| years4 = 2003\u20132004 | clubs4 = \u2192 [[FC Barcelona|Barcelona]] (loan) | caps4 = 1 | goals4 = 0\n| years5 = 2006\u20132007 | clubs5 = [[Recreativo de Huelva|Recreativo]] | caps5 = 24 | goals5 = 1\n| years6 = 2007\u20132011 | clubs6 = [[Getafe CF|Getafe]] | caps6 = 59 | goals6 = 0\n| years7 = 2011\u20132013 | clubs7 = [[Real Betis|Betis]] | caps7 = 32 | goals7 = 1   \n| years8 = 2013\u20132014 | clubs8 = [[Baku FC|Baku]] | caps8 = 30 | goals8 = 2\n| years9 = 2014\u20132016 | clubs9 = [[Real Zaragoza|Zaragoza]] | caps9 = 31 | goals9 = 0\n| years10 = 2016\u20132017 | clubs10 = [[Muangthong United F.C.|Muangthong United]] | caps10 = 19 | goals10 = 1\n| years11 = 2017 | clubs11 = [[BEC Tero Sasana F.C.|BEC Tero Sasana]] | caps11 = 24 | goals11 = 1\n| years12 = 2018\u2013 | clubs12 = [[Atl\u00e9tico San Luis]] | caps12 = 55 | goals12 = 0\n| totalcaps = | totalgoals = \n| nationalyears1 = 1998\u20131999 | nationalteam1 = [[Spain national under-16 football team|Spain U16]] | nationalcaps1 = 9 | nationalgoals1 = 1\n| nationalyears2 = 1999 | nationalteam2 = [[Spain national under-17 football team|Spain U17]] | nationalcaps2 = 2 | nationalgoals2 = 1\n| nationalyears3 = 2000\u20132001 | nationalteam3 = [[Spain national under-18 football team|Spain U18]] | nationalcaps3 = 7 | nationalgoals3 = 0\n| nationalyears4 = 2002\u20132003 | nationalteam4 = [[Spain national under-21 football team|Spain U21]] | nationalcaps4 = 5 | nationalgoals4 = 0\n| club-update = 24 February 2020\n}}\n'''Pedro Mario \u00c1lvarez Abrante''' (born 2 February 1982), commonly known as '''Mario''', is a Spanish professional [[Association football|footballer]] as a [[Defender (association football)#Centre-back|central defender]] for Mexican club [[Atl\u00e9tico San Luis]].\n\n==Club career==\nBorn in [[Santa Cruz de Tenerife]], [[Canary Islands]], Mario started his senior career with [[Atl\u00e9tico Madrid]], but could only represent its [[Atl\u00e9tico Madrid C|C]] and [[Atl\u00e9tico Madrid B|B-teams]]. In summer 2001 he signed for [[Real Valladolid]], making his [[La Liga]] debut in the [[2001\u201302 La Liga|2001\u201302 season]], playing in 17 games and repeating the feat [[2002\u201303 La Liga|the following campaign]], still in the top flight.\n\nIn [[2003\u201304 La Liga|2003\u201304]], Mario was loaned to [[FC Barcelona]],<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.lavanguardia.com/deportes/20030811/51262779669/el-barca-incorpora-al-central-mario-cedido-por-el-valladolid.html|title=El Bar\u00e7a incorpora al central Mario, cedido por el Valladolid|trans-title=Bar\u00e7a add centre-back Mario, loaned by Valladolid|publisher=[[La Vanguardia]]|language=Spanish|date=11 August 2003|accessdate=17 April 2020}}</ref> appearing only once for the [[Catalonia|Catalans]] officially, in an infamous 1\u20135 away defeat against [[M\u00e1laga CF]] on 3 December 2003.<ref>[http://www.elmundo.es/elmundodeporte/2003/12/03/liga/1070477534.html El M\u00e1laga deja en coma al Barcelona antes del cl\u00e1sico (M\u00e1laga leave Barcelona in a coma before ''cl\u00e1sico'')]; El Mundo, 4 December 2003 (in Spanish)</ref> As Valladolid were relegated in June he returned to the [[Castile and Le\u00f3n]] club for two further seasons, both spent in [[Segunda Divisi\u00f3n]].\n\nMario joined [[Recreativo de Huelva]] in 2006, being an important defensive element as the [[Andalusia]]n side [[2006\u201307 La Liga|finished eighth]] in the top level, while scoring his fifth goal as a senior on 5 November 2006 in a [[Last-minute goal|last minute]] 2\u20131 home win over [[Gimn\u00e0stic de Tarragona]].<ref>[http://soccernet.espn.go.com/report?id=204996&cc=5739 Recreativo Huelva 2\u20131 Gimnastic de Tarragona]; [[ESPN FC|ESPN Soccernet]], 5 November 2006</ref>\n\nFor the [[2007\u201308 La Liga|2007\u201308 season]], Mario signed with [[Getafe CF]],<ref>[http://www.uefa.com/uefaeuropaleague/news/newsid=562213.html Getafe get Mario from Recreativo]; UEFA, 18 July 2007</ref> being an undisputed starter in [[2008\u201309 La Liga|his second year]] but appearing rarely the following campaigns due to constant injuries.<ref>[http://futbol.as.com/futbol/2010/10/02/mas_futbol/1286000853_850215.html Mario se despide de la temporada por lesi\u00f3n (Mario says goodbye to season due to injury)]; [[Diario AS]], 2 October 2010 (in Spanish)</ref><ref>[http://www.marca.com/2011/03/09/futbol/equipos/getafe/1299700991.html Mario: \"La lesi\u00f3n ha sido lo peor que he tenido en mi vida\" (Mario: \"The injury has been the worst that has happened in my life\")]; [[Marca (newspaper)|Marca]], 9 March 2011 (in Spanish)</ref> His first appearance in [[2010\u201311 La Liga|2010\u201311]] \u2013 one of just three<ref>{{cite news|url=https://elpais.com/deportes/2011/06/10/actualidad/1307690527_850215.html|title=Mario, el \u00faltimo legado de Belenguer|trans-title=Mario, Belenguer's last legacy|publisher=[[El Pa\u00eds]]|language=Spanish|date=1 July 2011|accessdate=17 April 2020}}</ref>\u2013 only took place on 10 May 2011, in a 0\u20134 away loss against [[Real Madrid CF|Real Madrid]].<ref>[http://soccernet.espn.go.com/report/_/id/301989?cc=5739 Madrid make Barca wait]; ESPN Soccernet, 10 May 2011</ref>\n\nMario also spent extended periods on the sidelines with his following team, [[Real Betis]], with which he signed as a [[free agent]] in June 2011.<ref>[http://www.abc.es/agencias/noticia.asp?noticia=844144 Ex jugador del Valladolid Mario (Getafe) ficha por el Betis (Ex-Valladolid player Mario (Getafe) signs with Betis)]; [[ABC (newspaper)|ABC]], 8 June 2011 (in Spanish)</ref><ref>[http://www.alfinaldelapalmera.com/noticias/real-betis/betis-temporada-2012-2013-mario-vuelve-entrenarse-resto-grupo-tras-getafe.html Mario vuelve a entrenarse con el resto del grupo (Mario returns to group training)]; Al Final de la Palmera, 6 November 2012 (in Spanish)</ref><ref>[http://www.marca.com/2012/07/13/futbol/equipos/betis/1342173380.html Mario se fractura el tercio medio de la clav\u00edcula (Mario fractures collarbone medial end)]; Marca, 13 July 2012 (in Spanish)</ref> He scored his first and only goal for the ''Verdiblancos'' on 24 February 2013 in a 3\u20130 home defeat of M\u00e1laga,<ref>[http://www.goal.com/es/match/85468/betis-vs-m%C3%A1laga/report Betis 3\u20130 M\u00e1laga: Reencuentro a lo grande con el gol (Betis 3\u20130 M\u00e1laga: Rediscovering scoring ways big time)]; [[Goal (website)|Goal]], 24 February 2013 (in Spanish)</ref> but his team was [[2012\u201313 La Liga|eventually relegated]] and he left.\n\nIn late July 2013, Mario signed a two-year contract with [[Azerbaijan Premier League]] side [[Baku FC]].<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.marca.com/2013/07/30/futbol/equipos/betis/1375184006.html|title=Mario firma dos a\u00f1os por el FC Bak\u00fa de Azerbaiy\u00e1n|trans-title=Mario signs for two years with Azerbaijan's Baku|publisher=Marca|language=Spanish|date=30 July 2013|accessdate=11 February 2016}}</ref> After featuring regularly he moved back to Spain, penning a two-year deal with [[Real Zaragoza]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.realzaragoza.com/noticias/44541|title=Mario \u00c1lvarez, nuevo jugador del Real Zaragoza|trans-title=Mario \u00c1lvarez, new player of Real Zaragoza|publisher=Real Zaragoza|language=Spanish|date=14 August 2014|accessdate=18 August 2014}}</ref>\n\nOn 8 March 2016, after one and a half seasons in the second level, Mario moved to the [[Thai Premier League]] with [[Muangthong United F.C.|Muangthong United FC]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://footballchannel.asia/2016/03/08/post9813/|title=Muangthong United signs former Barcelona defender Mario Abrante|publisher=Football Channel Asia|first=Arwatchanon|last=Insawang|date=8 March 2016|accessdate=8 March 2016}}</ref>\n\n==Honours==\n===Club===\n'''Muangthong United'''\n*[[Thai Premier League]]: [[2016 Thai Premier League|2016]]\n*[[Thai League Cup]]: [[2016 Thai League Cup|2016]]\n*[[Thailand Champions Cup]]: [[2017 Thailand Champions Cup|2017]]\n\n===International===\n'''Spain U16'''\n*[[UEFA European Under-17 Championship|UEFA European Under-16 Championship]]: [[1999 UEFA European Under-16 Championship|1999]]<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.rsssf.com/tablese/ec-u16-99.html|title=European U-16 Championship 1999|publisher=[[RSSSF]]|first=Josef|last=Bobrowsky|accessdate=17 April 2020}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*{{BDFutbol|1905|Mario}}\n*{{Futbolme profile|7895|Mario}}\n*{{FIFA player|175417|Mario}}\n*{{Soccerway|pedro-mario-alvarez-abrante/4555|Mario}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Mario Abrante}}\n[[Category:1982 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Sportspeople from Santa Cruz de Tenerife]]\n[[Category:Spanish footballers]]\n[[Category:Canarian footballers]]\n[[Category:Association football central defenders]]\n[[Category:La Liga players]]\n[[Category:Segunda Divisi\u00f3n players]]\n[[Category:Segunda Divisi\u00f3n B players]]\n[[Category:Atl\u00e9tico Madrid C players]]\n[[Category:Atl\u00e9tico Madrid B players]]\n[[Category:Real Valladolid players]]\n[[Category:FC Barcelona players]]\n[[Category:Recreativo de Huelva players]]\n[[Category:Getafe CF footballers]]\n[[Category:Real Betis players]]\n[[Category:Real Zaragoza players]]\n[[Category:Azerbaijan Premier League players]]\n[[Category:FC Baku players]]\n[[Category:Thai League 1 players]]\n[[Category:Muangthong United F.C. players]]\n[[Category:Police Tero F.C. players]]\n[[Category:Liga MX players]]\n[[Category:San Luis F.C. players]]\n[[Category:Spain youth international footballers]]\n[[Category:Spain under-21 international footballers]]\n[[Category:Spanish expatriate footballers]]\n[[Category:Expatriate footballers in Azerbaijan]]\n[[Category:Expatriate footballers in Thailand]]\n[[Category:Expatriate footballers in Mexico]]\n[[Category:Spanish expatriate sportspeople in Azerbaijan]]\n[[Category:Spanish expatriate sportspeople in Thailand]]\n[[Category:Spanish expatriate sportspeople in Mexico]]\n", "text_old": "{{Spanish name|\u00c1lvarez|Abrante}}\n{{Infobox football biography\n| name = Mario\n| image = Mario 2011.jpg\n| image_size = 150\n| caption = Mario as a [[Real Betis|Betis]] player in 2011\n| fullname = Pedro Mario \u00c1lvarez Abrante<ref name=Bio>{{cite news|url=https://www.elmundo.es/elmundodeporte/envivos/fichas/1/020/4372.html|title=Pedro MARIO \u00c1lvarez Abrante|publisher=[[El Mundo (Spain)|El Mundo]]|language=Spanish|accessdate=17 April 2020}}</ref>\n| birth_date = {{birth date and age|1982|2|2|df=y}}<ref name=Bio/>\n| birth_place = [[Tenerife]], Spain<ref name=Bio/>\n| height = {{height|m=1.78}}<ref name=Bio/>\n| position = [[Defender (association football)#Centre-back|Centre back]]\n| currentclub = [[Atl\u00e9tico San Luis]]\n| clubnumber = 5\n| youthyears1 = | youthclubs1 = Longuera-Toscal\n| youthyears2 = 1998\u20131999 | youthclubs2 = [[Atl\u00e9tico Madrid]]\n| years1 = 1999\u20132000 | clubs1 = [[Atl\u00e9tico Madrid C]] | caps1 = | goals1 = \n| years2 = 2000\u20132001 | clubs2 = [[Atl\u00e9tico Madrid B]] | caps2 = 28 | goals2 = 0\n| years3 = 2001\u20132006 | clubs3 = [[Real Valladolid|Valladolid]] | caps3 = 90 | goals3 = 3\n| years4 = 2003\u20132004 | clubs4 = \u2192 [[FC Barcelona|Barcelona]] (loan) | caps4 = 1 | goals4 = 0\n| years5 = 2006\u20132007 | clubs5 = [[Recreativo de Huelva|Recreativo]] | caps5 = 24 | goals5 = 1\n| years6 = 2007\u20132011 | clubs6 = [[Getafe CF|Getafe]] | caps6 = 59 | goals6 = 0\n| years7 = 2011\u20132013 | clubs7 = [[Real Betis|Betis]] | caps7 = 32 | goals7 = 1   \n| years8 = 2013\u20132014 | clubs8 = [[Baku FC|Baku]] | caps8 = 30 | goals8 = 2\n| years9 = 2014\u20132016 | clubs9 = [[Real Zaragoza|Zaragoza]] | caps9 = 31 | goals9 = 0\n| years10 = 2016 | clubs10 = [[Muangthong United F.C.|Muangthong United]] | caps10 = 19 | goals10 = 1\n| years11 = 2017 | clubs11 = [[BEC Tero Sasana F.C.|BEC Tero Sasana]] | caps11 = 24 | goals11 = 1\n| years12 = 2018\u2013 | clubs12 = [[Atl\u00e9tico San Luis]] | caps12 = 55 | goals12 = 0\n| totalcaps = | totalgoals = \n| nationalyears1 = 1998\u20131999 | nationalteam1 = [[Spain national under-16 football team|Spain U16]] | nationalcaps1 = 9 | nationalgoals1 = 1\n| nationalyears2 = 1999 | nationalteam2 = [[Spain national under-17 football team|Spain U17]] | nationalcaps2 = 2 | nationalgoals2 = 1\n| nationalyears3 = 2000\u20132001 | nationalteam3 = [[Spain national under-18 football team|Spain U18]] | nationalcaps3 = 7 | nationalgoals3 = 0\n| nationalyears4 = 2002\u20132003 | nationalteam4 = [[Spain national under-21 football team|Spain U21]] | nationalcaps4 = 5 | nationalgoals4 = 0\n| club-update = 24 February 2020\n}}\n'''Pedro Mario \u00c1lvarez Abrante''' (born 2 February 1982), commonly known as '''Mario''', is a Spanish professional [[Association football|footballer]] as a [[Defender (association football)#Centre-back|central defender]] for Mexican club [[Atl\u00e9tico San Luis]].\n\n==Club career==\nBorn in [[Santa Cruz de Tenerife]], [[Canary Islands]], Mario started his senior career with [[Atl\u00e9tico Madrid]], but could only represent its [[Atl\u00e9tico Madrid C|C]] and [[Atl\u00e9tico Madrid B|B-teams]]. In summer 2001 he signed for [[Real Valladolid]], making his [[La Liga]] debut in the [[2001\u201302 La Liga|2001\u201302 season]], playing in 17 games and repeating the feat [[2002\u201303 La Liga|the following campaign]], still in the top flight.\n\nIn [[2003\u201304 La Liga|2003\u201304]], Mario was loaned to [[FC Barcelona]],<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.lavanguardia.com/deportes/20030811/51262779669/el-barca-incorpora-al-central-mario-cedido-por-el-valladolid.html|title=El Bar\u00e7a incorpora al central Mario, cedido por el Valladolid|trans-title=Bar\u00e7a add centre-back Mario, loaned by Valladolid|publisher=[[La Vanguardia]]|language=Spanish|date=11 August 2003|accessdate=17 April 2020}}</ref> appearing only once for the [[Catalonia|Catalans]] officially, in an infamous 1\u20135 away defeat against [[M\u00e1laga CF]] on 3 December 2003.<ref>[http://www.elmundo.es/elmundodeporte/2003/12/03/liga/1070477534.html El M\u00e1laga deja en coma al Barcelona antes del cl\u00e1sico (M\u00e1laga leave Barcelona in a coma before ''cl\u00e1sico'')]; El Mundo, 4 December 2003 (in Spanish)</ref> As Valladolid were relegated in June he returned to the [[Castile and Le\u00f3n]] club for two further seasons, both spent in [[Segunda Divisi\u00f3n]].\n\nMario joined [[Recreativo de Huelva]] in 2006, being an important defensive element as the [[Andalusia]]n side [[2006\u201307 La Liga|finished eighth]] in the top level, while scoring his fifth goal as a senior on 5 November 2006 in a [[Last-minute goal|last minute]] 2\u20131 home win over [[Gimn\u00e0stic de Tarragona]].<ref>[http://soccernet.espn.go.com/report?id=204996&cc=5739 Recreativo Huelva 2\u20131 Gimnastic de Tarragona]; [[ESPN FC|ESPN Soccernet]], 5 November 2006</ref>\n\nFor the [[2007\u201308 La Liga|2007\u201308 season]], Mario signed with [[Getafe CF]],<ref>[http://www.uefa.com/uefaeuropaleague/news/newsid=562213.html Getafe get Mario from Recreativo]; UEFA, 18 July 2007</ref> being an undisputed starter in [[2008\u201309 La Liga|his second year]] but appearing rarely the following campaigns due to constant injuries.<ref>[http://futbol.as.com/futbol/2010/10/02/mas_futbol/1286000853_850215.html Mario se despide de la temporada por lesi\u00f3n (Mario says goodbye to season due to injury)]; [[Diario AS]], 2 October 2010 (in Spanish)</ref><ref>[http://www.marca.com/2011/03/09/futbol/equipos/getafe/1299700991.html Mario: \"La lesi\u00f3n ha sido lo peor que he tenido en mi vida\" (Mario: \"The injury has been the worst that has happened in my life\")]; [[Marca (newspaper)|Marca]], 9 March 2011 (in Spanish)</ref> His first appearance in [[2010\u201311 La Liga|2010\u201311]] \u2013 one of just three<ref>{{cite news|url=https://elpais.com/deportes/2011/06/10/actualidad/1307690527_850215.html|title=Mario, el \u00faltimo legado de Belenguer|trans-title=Mario, Belenguer's last legacy|publisher=[[El Pa\u00eds]]|language=Spanish|date=1 July 2011|accessdate=17 April 2020}}</ref>\u2013 only took place on 10 May 2011, in a 0\u20134 away loss against [[Real Madrid CF|Real Madrid]].<ref>[http://soccernet.espn.go.com/report/_/id/301989?cc=5739 Madrid make Barca wait]; ESPN Soccernet, 10 May 2011</ref>\n\nMario also spent extended periods on the sidelines with his following team, [[Real Betis]], with which he signed as a [[free agent]] in June 2011.<ref>[http://www.abc.es/agencias/noticia.asp?noticia=844144 Ex jugador del Valladolid Mario (Getafe) ficha por el Betis (Ex-Valladolid player Mario (Getafe) signs with Betis)]; [[ABC (newspaper)|ABC]], 8 June 2011 (in Spanish)</ref><ref>[http://www.alfinaldelapalmera.com/noticias/real-betis/betis-temporada-2012-2013-mario-vuelve-entrenarse-resto-grupo-tras-getafe.html Mario vuelve a entrenarse con el resto del grupo (Mario returns to group training)]; Al Final de la Palmera, 6 November 2012 (in Spanish)</ref><ref>[http://www.marca.com/2012/07/13/futbol/equipos/betis/1342173380.html Mario se fractura el tercio medio de la clav\u00edcula (Mario fractures collarbone medial end)]; Marca, 13 July 2012 (in Spanish)</ref> He scored his first and only goal for the ''Verdiblancos'' on 24 February 2013 in a 3\u20130 home defeat of M\u00e1laga,<ref>[http://www.goal.com/es/match/85468/betis-vs-m%C3%A1laga/report Betis 3\u20130 M\u00e1laga: Reencuentro a lo grande con el gol (Betis 3\u20130 M\u00e1laga: Rediscovering scoring ways big time)]; [[Goal (website)|Goal]], 24 February 2013 (in Spanish)</ref> but his team was [[2012\u201313 La Liga|eventually relegated]] and he left.\n\nIn late July 2013, Mario signed a two-year contract with [[Azerbaijan Premier League]] side [[Baku FC]].<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.marca.com/2013/07/30/futbol/equipos/betis/1375184006.html|title=Mario firma dos a\u00f1os por el FC Bak\u00fa de Azerbaiy\u00e1n|trans-title=Mario signs for two years with Azerbaijan's Baku|publisher=Marca|language=Spanish|date=30 July 2013|accessdate=11 February 2016}}</ref> After featuring regularly he moved back to Spain, penning a two-year deal with [[Real Zaragoza]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.realzaragoza.com/noticias/44541|title=Mario \u00c1lvarez, nuevo jugador del Real Zaragoza|trans-title=Mario \u00c1lvarez, new player of Real Zaragoza|publisher=Real Zaragoza|language=Spanish|date=14 August 2014|accessdate=18 August 2014}}</ref>\n\nOn 8 March 2016, after one and a half seasons in the second level, Mario moved to the [[Thai Premier League]] with [[Muangthong United F.C.|Muangthong United FC]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://footballchannel.asia/2016/03/08/post9813/|title=Muangthong United signs former Barcelona defender Mario Abrante|publisher=Football Channel Asia|first=Arwatchanon|last=Insawang|date=8 March 2016|accessdate=8 March 2016}}</ref>\n\n==Honours==\n===Club===\n'''Muangthong United'''\n*[[Thai Premier League]]: [[2016 Thai Premier League|2016]]\n*[[Thai League Cup]]: [[2016 Thai League Cup|2016]]\n*[[Thailand Champions Cup]]: [[2017 Thailand Champions Cup|2017]]\n\n===International===\n'''Spain U16'''\n*[[UEFA European Under-17 Championship|UEFA European Under-16 Championship]]: [[1999 UEFA European Under-16 Championship|1999]]<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.rsssf.com/tablese/ec-u16-99.html|title=European U-16 Championship 1999|publisher=[[RSSSF]]|first=Josef|last=Bobrowsky|accessdate=17 April 2020}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*{{BDFutbol|1905|Mario}}\n*{{Futbolme profile|7895|Mario}}\n*{{FIFA player|175417|Mario}}\n*{{Soccerway|pedro-mario-alvarez-abrante/4555|Mario}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Mario Abrante}}\n[[Category:1982 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Sportspeople from Santa Cruz de Tenerife]]\n[[Category:Spanish footballers]]\n[[Category:Canarian footballers]]\n[[Category:Association football central defenders]]\n[[Category:La Liga players]]\n[[Category:Segunda Divisi\u00f3n players]]\n[[Category:Segunda Divisi\u00f3n B players]]\n[[Category:Atl\u00e9tico Madrid C players]]\n[[Category:Atl\u00e9tico Madrid B players]]\n[[Category:Real Valladolid players]]\n[[Category:FC Barcelona players]]\n[[Category:Recreativo de Huelva players]]\n[[Category:Getafe CF footballers]]\n[[Category:Real Betis players]]\n[[Category:Real Zaragoza players]]\n[[Category:Azerbaijan Premier League players]]\n[[Category:FC Baku players]]\n[[Category:Thai League 1 players]]\n[[Category:Muangthong United F.C. players]]\n[[Category:Police Tero F.C. players]]\n[[Category:Liga MX players]]\n[[Category:San Luis F.C. players]]\n[[Category:Spain youth international footballers]]\n[[Category:Spain under-21 international footballers]]\n[[Category:Spanish expatriate footballers]]\n[[Category:Expatriate footballers in Aze